Soyin and I have been pretty much a fixture there most nights since the Trade Fair.  It's a very good area for anybody from the high teens, grouped, to low 20 to mid 20's solo. I first went there at 22 and got 2 blue bulbs of experience per kill. I just had to wait to heal to full health before I started again. there was hardly anybody else in the zone. I recruited Soyin  to join me and we were still getting good xp together.<br>
 the  bandits aggro on anything, but rogues. If you are a rogue and are fighting either the mushrooms, yelloweyes, or the potarg phlarg fiends, the bandits will join in and kill whatever you are fighting.  The fiends, which are sometimes trained to the zoneline to shadowhaven through our group, have a nasty disease, which acts like a DOT. It's called the spreading crud and if you are standing, it takes 2 hp's per tick. zero if you are resting, but it lasts for hours. I went through 3 stacks of bandages before it went away. Soyin caught it and was lucky enough to find a cleric to cure her. <br>
I haven't really left the zone entrance to shadowhaven yet, to explore the rest of the caverns, But I here there is a named muchroom someplace in there. There is also Maricellis Slithera who drops an ancient ornate combine dagger which is part of the crypt robbers quests. <br>
<br>
I highly reccomend the area to anybody who needs to jump up a few levels fast or needs money. The area seems to fall in between the orcs, and the goblins in the basement, in Highpass.<br>
<br>
Wiestrum<br>
Rogue of the 25th Circle<br>
